Flexbox makes layout easy! Here are some quick tips:

• Use justify-content: center to center items horizontally.
• Use align-items: center to center items vertically.
• Use flex-wrap: wrap so items don't overflow on small screens.
• Use gap to create spacing between elements instead of margin hacks.

.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 1rem;
}

Tip: Always use Flexbox for one-dimensional layouts (row or column).

Debouncing helps improve performance by limiting how often a function runs.

Use case: Search input, resize events.

function debounce(fn, delay) {
  let timer;
  return function(...args) {
    clearTimeout(timer);
    timer = setTimeout(() => fn.apply(this, args), delay);
  };
}

Example:
const handleSearch = debounce((e) => {
  console.log(e.target.value);
}, 500);

Tip: Prevents unnecessary API calls and improves UX.

Media queries help you make your website responsive.

Example:

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .container {
    flex-direction: column;
  }
}

Tip: Always design mobile-first for better scalability.

Async/Await makes asynchronous code cleaner and readable.

Example:

async function fetchData() {
  try {
    const res = await fetch('https://api.example.com');
    const data = await res.json();
    console.log(data);
  } catch (err) {
    console.error(err);
  }
}

Tip: Avoid callback hell and write cleaner code.

LocalStorage allows you to store data in the browser.

Example:

localStorage.setItem('username', 'Hariom');
const user = localStorage.getItem('username');
console.log(user);

Tip: Useful for saving user preferences like theme or login state.
